      "text": "Meta is rolling out a feature called [[Personal Boundary]] in its Horizon Worlds and Horizon Venues virtual reality spaces. Each avatar will have a bubble with a radius of two virtual feet, so they won’t be able to come within around four feet of each other. Users won't be able to disable this. So fist bumping is still possible if you stretch out your arms, hugging is a no-no.\n"
